## Payment Flow

### Complete Payment Flow Diagram

```
1. User selects "Make Payment" on a trust
   ↓
2. Payment Form Modal opens
   ↓
3. User enters payment amount (validated: max RM 30,000 per transaction)
   ↓
4. User clicks "Continue to Payment"
   ↓
5. App calls getChipClient() to get/create CHIP customer ID
   ↓
6. App calls addChipPayment() with:
   - trustId
   - trustCode
   - amount (in cents)
   - clientId (from step 5)
   ↓
7. Backend creates payment record in trust_payments (status: 'initiated')
   ↓
8. Backend calls CHIP API to create purchase
   ↓
9. Backend updates trust_payments with chip_payment_id
   ↓
10. Backend returns checkout_url
    ↓
11. App opens checkout_url in WebView or external browser
    ↓
12. User completes payment on CHIP gateway
    ↓
13. CHIP redirects to success_url or failure_url
    ↓
14. CHIP sends webhook to success_callback endpoint
    ↓
15. Backend updates payment status via webhook
    ↓
16. App shows payment status modal (success/failure)
    ↓
17. App refreshes trust data to show updated payment history
```

